author: Elizabeth Chuck
description: Thomas Pinkerton, a former youth minister known as Pastor Tommy, is accused of sexually abusing at least six boys from 2006 to 2010 while working at Central Christian Church, an Assemblies of God church in Baltimore County, Maryland.
title: Former youth pastor arrested after allegedly sexually abusing at least 6 teens

author: The Associated Press
description: TEL AVIV, Israel — New video footage appears to show the moment a Palestinian activist was killed as an Israeli settler fired toward him during a confrontation with unarmed Palestinians in the occupied West Bank last month
title: Video appears to show the moment a Palestinian activist is killed as an Israeli settler opens fire

author: Steve Kopack
description: The announcement comes after Trump fired the previous Bureau of Labor Statistics commissioner, claiming without evidence that the July jobs report was "rigged."
title: Trump to nominate conservative economist E.J. Antoni as new commissioner of labor statistics

author: Eric Mullin, NBCUniversal Local
description: Cristiano Ronaldo has gotten engaged to his longtime girlfriend Georgina Rodríguez.
title: Cristiano Ronaldo proposes to his longtime girlfriend with massive engagement ring

author: The Associated Press
description: CAIRO — Sudan’s paramilitary Rapid Support Forces launched attacks Monday in a famine-stricken displacement camp outside of el-Fasher, the capital of North Darfur province, killing 40 people, local rights groups said
title: Sudan's Rapid Support Forces kill 40 people in North Darfur displacement camp attack

author: The Associated Press
description: DAKAR, Senegal — It’s the largest piece of Mars ever found on Earth — a 54-pound (25-kilogram) meteorite that fetched more than $5 million at a New York auction last month, setting a world record
title: Why Niger is investigating the $5 million sale of the largest Mars rock found on Earth

author: The Politics Desk
description: Donald Trump isn’t the first president to deploy troops and federal agents in the name of safeguarding the nation’s capital, but he has been particularly selective about what represents a threat to the peace.
title: The political — and historical — context of Trump's D.C. crackdown: From the Politics Desk

author: Phil Helsel
description: Three people were killed Monday afternoon in a shooting outside a Target store, and the suspect was arrested after stealing a car and fleeing the scene in Austin, Texas, police said
title: 3 killed in Austin Target shooting; suspect is detained

description: NBC News Senior National Security Correspondent Courtney Kube joins Meet the Press NOW with the latest on President Trump and Russian President Putin’s meeting which is set to take place on Friday in Alaska.
title: Zelenskyy has ‘no intention’ of ceding territory with Trump and Putin set to hold talks

author: Sandra Lilley
description: Colombian rapper Maluma stopped a concert in Mexico City to chastise one of his own fans for bringing her infant to his show and exposing the tyke to high decibel levels
title: Rapper Maluma stops show to call out mother for bringing infant to his Mexico City concert

author: Melissa Chan
description: A Texas woman is suing a U.S. Marine, alleging he spiked her drink with nearly a dozen abortion pills, killing their unborn child, after she rebuffed his repeated requests to “get rid of it.”
title: Texas woman sues Marine, claiming he spiked her drink with abortion pills

description: Mayor Muriel Bowser held a press conference to address President Trump's announcement of his plans to put the city's police under federal control and deploy the National Guard to address crime in the city. The mayor called the president's plans "unsettling and unprecedented," but admitted she was not totally surprised by the decisions being made.
title: Mayor Bowser says Trump's plan for D.C. crime is 'unsettling and unprecedented'

author: Katherine Doyle
description: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump said Monday that he would try to return territory to Ukraine as he prepares to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin and lay the groundwork for a deal to bring an end to the grinding multiyear war between Ukraine and Russia.“Russia has occupied a big portion of Ukraine.
title: Ahead of Putin sitdown, Trump says he hopes to get 'prime territory' back for Ukraine

author: Mirna Alsharif
description: A New York man who was fatally shot in Puerto Rico's La Perla neighborhood in San Juan on Sunday is being remembered by his loved ones as a beloved son, friend and inspiration to all who knew him
title: New York man fatally shot while in Puerto Rico for Bad Bunny concert remembered as inspiration

author: Minyvonne Burke
description: An explosion occurred Monday at a steel factory in the Pittsburgh area, leaving people trapped in the rubble, officials said.
title: Explosion at a Pennsylvania steel factory prompts rescue operation

author: Mirna Alsharif
description: A surprise guest of the creepy crawly variety made an appearance at Jennifer Lopez's latest concert in Kazakhstan
title: Video shows cricket crawling on Jennifer Lopez during Kazakhstan concert

author: Berkeley Lovelace Jr.
description: CDC staffers are voicing frustration over RFK Jr.’s past vaccine comments, following Friday’s shooting at the agency’s headquarters in Atlanta that left one officer dead.
title: CDC staffers voice frustration over RFK Jr.'s anti-vaccine rhetoric in wake of shooting

description: President Donald Trump told reporters Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy would not be in attendance during a meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports that Trump plans to call Zelenskyy and other European leaders after the meeting with Putin.
title: Trump says Zelenskyy not invited to meeting with Putin

description: President Trump said that homeless encampments will be removed from Washington, D.C., parks and underpasses as part of his promised crackdown on crime in the city.
title: Trump vows to remove D.C. homeless encampments

author: Matt Bradley
description: Outrage is growing over Benjamin Netanyahu’s planned Gaza Strip offensive, with anger at home matching condemnation abroad for the Israeli prime minister.
title: Netanyahu's plans for expanded Gaza offensive spark anger and dismay at home and abroad

description: President Trump announced that he would "bring the military" into the U.S. capital if necessary after he announced that the D.C. police would come under federal control to combat crime. The president emphasized that he doesn't think the military will be needed, but he would be ready to deploy it. "People say, 'Oh, that's so terrible. He's going to bring in.' It's been used many times over the years. I don't think we'll need it," Trump told reporters.
title: Trump says he'll bring the military into D.C. if necessary

author: David K. Li
description: New York police on Monday were still looking for a man who threw a sex toy during a WNBA game, striking a little girl in attendance, officials said
title: 12-year-old girl struck by sex toy thrown at WNBA game in Brooklyn; suspect sought by NYPD

author: Kaitlin Sullivan
description: In an early trial, a one-size-fits-all vaccine showed promise in preventing hard-to-treat pancreatic cancers from coming back
title: One-size-fits-all pancreatic cancer vaccine showed promise in early trial

author: David K. Li
description: Country star Zach Bryan vowed over the weekend he'll fly like an Eagle over Kansas City and never play that town again
title: Country star Zach Bryan vows to never play Kansas City in spat with Chiefs fans

author: Alexander Smith
description: European leaders are trying to get Ukraine's President Volodymyr Zelenskyy invited to Trump and Putin's summit in Alaska.
title: Europe fears Ukraine — and itself — are being excluded from Trump-Putin talks

author: Chloe Atkins
description: A federal judge on Monday denied the Department of Justice’s request to unseal grand jury materials in Ghislaine Maxwell’s criminal case
title: Judge denies DOJ bid to unseal Ghislaine Maxwell grand jury records

author: Alex Sherman, CNBC
description: Days after completing its merger with Skydance, Paramount has acquired the U.S. rights to TKO Group’s UFC for seven years, beginning in 2026
title: Paramount buys UFC rights in $7.7 billion deal

author: Minyvonne Burke
description: Two blind women traveling from Louisiana to Florida said that Southwest Airlines "forgot" them at the airport following a nearly five-hour flight delay.
title: 2 blind women say Southwest Airlines left them behind following hourslong delay

description: Watch live coverage as President Trump holds a news conference to discuss his administration's plan to address crime in Washington, D.C. The president is considering deploying 1,000 National Guard troops to the nations capital, according to U.S. officials, and has warned people experiencing homelessness to leave the district.
title: Trump holds news conference on crime in D.C.

description: AOL, once known for its squawk, squeal and chirp when logging on, announces it is pulling the plug on its dial-up service at the end of September after a run that started back in 1991.
title: AOL to Pull the Plug on Its Dial-up Service in September

description: A community is mourning following the fatal shooting of DeKalb County Police Officer David Rose, a 33-year-old killed in the line of duty responding to a gunman that opened fire in Atlanta on Friday near the campuses of the CDC and Emory University. NBC’s Priya Sridhar reports for TODAY on details about the suspect.
title: CDC Employees Say Misinformation Led to Fatal Shooting

author: Kayla Hayempour
description: Trump ramps up law enforcement in D.C. after threats to take federal control. Netanyahu denies starvation in Gaza and defends military plans.
title: Trump considers deploying National Guard to D.C. and pressure mounts on Netanyahu: Morning Rundown

description: A dramatic high-speed chase unfolded on a California freeway with police in pursuit of carjackers who took over a series on vehicles, including a semitruck. Eventually, the suspects, who remain on the loose, ditched the big rig and stole a pickup truck near Downtown Los Angeles before moving the chase to a neighborhood. NBC’s Camila Bernal reports for TODAY.
title: Series of Carjackings in LA Leads to High-Speed Chase on Live TV

description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu addressed the public about his plans to expand military operations in Gaza, defending the move saying he remains focused in bringing hostages home. “Our goal is not to occupy Gaza. Our goal is to free Gaza, free it from Hamas terrorists,” he says. It comes as outrage grows over the worsening starvation crisis and rising malnutrition deaths in the territory. NBC’s Matt Bradley reports for TODAY.
title: Netanyahu: Military Expansion in Gaza Is to ‘Free It From Hamas’

description: President Donald Trump ordered the deployment nearly 500 federal law enforcement officers around Washington, D.C, over the weekend. He justified the move by setting the need to tackle persistent crime in the nation’s capital, but D.C.’s police data shows violent crime is down 26% compared to last year. NBC’s Garrett Haake reports for TODAY.
title: Trump Orders Deployment of Federal Law Enforcement Across DC

author: Megan Lebowitz
description: President Donald Trump will hold a news conference this morning about making Washington, D.C. "safer and more beautiful," he announced on Truth Social.
title: Trump to announce plans to address crime in D.C. after increasing federal law enforcement

description: Severe summer weather wreaked havoc across the United States over the weekend, with parts of the Midwest getting hammered by torrential rain and some parts of the west coast of Florida seeing up to eight inches of rain. The Wisconsin State Fair was shut down due to flooded parking lots after other parts of the state were soaked with a record 14 inches in 24 hours. NBC’s Maggie Vespa reports and TODAY’s Dylan Dreyer tracks the latest forecast.
title: Wisconsin Soaked With 14 Inches of Rain in 24 Hours

description: The President is set to hold a press event on crime after threatening a federal takeover of the capital.
title: Trump considers deploying up to 1,000 National Guard to D.C.

author: Matt Lavietes
description: Jacob Zieben-Hood was found dead and stabbed in his Harlem apartment in July after his husband called 911. His friends tell NBC News they were cut out years ago.
title: Model's husband was isolated for years before he was found dead in NYC apartment, friends say

author: Phil Helsel
description: In the hazy impressions of memory, some may even recall it fondly: The AOL dial-up internet service that those of a certain age associate with the World Wide Web is coming to a close
title: AOL ditching dial-up service, a relic of the internet in the '90s and early '00s

author: Jennifer Jett
description: Australia said Monday that it plans to recognize a Palestinian state, joining a growing list of Western governments making the move as Israel becomes increasingly isolated over the humanitarian crisis in the Gaza Strip
title: Australia says it plans to recognize a Palestinian state
